<subSubSection id="4094FDA687267CF3BD669235F85B5756" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AC64C9A405B657A67506F695B9B66F0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0C4F345D5C763F46D7590539D862A5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
This subspecies differs from 
<taxonomicName id="3D8E471DA513AA694AF1A4AADFBD8D74" authorityName="Jaklitsch &amp; Voglmayr" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis subsp. europaea" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="europaea">Melanconis marginalis subsp. europaea</taxonomicName>
and subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="AFDADD20FF1AA07426D5921EF35D0E72" authorityName="subsp. marginalis (Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="subsp. marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="marginalis">marginalis</taxonomicName>
phylogenetically and by slightly larger 
<normalizedToken id="B66CB99012686D54F96D7C0C848475DC" originalValue="α-conidia">α-conidia</normalizedToken>
, asci, ascospores and ascospore appendages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
