<subSubSection id="79B7BDCFBC719AB3669CB6891B78FFB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AE01CC65FADCA31BC61FC7FF326B677B" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B12E48BF16D6DED23C4C44428EA8855" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
As this subspecies differs morphologically only subtly from the other varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="B5C6D060573FF26065F27C925F036718" genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="0336295C9DDFE59D18112D248C201503" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we prefer to classify it as a subspecies rather than a separate species. While the ITS sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="2CF41A003769A2A4DE898E1659CED610" authorityName="Jaklitsch &amp; Voglmayr" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis subsp. tirolensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="tirolensis">Melanconis marginalis subsp. tirolensis</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="747117A9685AB8C7F8766A2D9FA78E5D" authorityName="Jaklitsch &amp; Voglmayr" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis subsp. europaea" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="europaea">Melanconis marginalis subsp. europaea</taxonomicName>
in only a single base pair, the differences are substantial in all other markers included, particularly 
<emphasis id="1F2A2F0DB65A2E33864BD4970CF975C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">tef1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B899997EF359A3CFA0CCC6D0FB1CF470" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">tub2</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
